                            <comment id="272570" author="adilger" created="Thu, 11 Jun 2020 08:12:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The Ubuntu 14/16 patches were removed from master in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38139&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38139&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12477&quot; title=&quot;Remove obsolete config checks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12477&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12477&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ldiskfs: last cleanups&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="243624" author="mhschroe" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2019 09:48:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your concern.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, since we need the changes internally anyway, it is not a lot of extra-effort to just do the &quot;git push&quot; when we&apos;re done. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="243554" author="pjones" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2019 16:25:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok I was just hoping to save you wasted effort in the event that people are disinclined to review/land these changes&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="243538" author="mhschroe" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2019 08:22:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t worry, I understand. I only raised this ticket to upstream the change myself later today.&#160;&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; Martin.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="243481" author="pjones" created="Thu, 7 Mar 2019 17:42:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Martin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our Ubuntu efforts for future community releases are focused on Ubuntu 18.04. Anyone wanting to run an older release like 14.04/16.04 would probably also want to run an older Lustre version&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
